• **pwd** Show current directory  
• **ls** List files  
• **ls -a** List all including hidden files  
• **cd /path/to/dir** Change directory  
• **cd ..** Go up one directory  
• **mkdir name** Create new directory  
• **rm filename** Remove file  
• **rm -r dirname** Remove directory  
• **cp source destination** Copy file or folder  
• **mv oldname newname** Move or rename file  
• **cat filename** Show contents of a file  
• **grep 'text' filename** Search inside files  
• **ps aux** Show running processes  
• **ps aux | grep name** Filter processes with grep  
• **kill PID** Kill process by PID  
• **clear** Clear terminal  
• **history** Show command history  
• **sudo !!** Re-run last command with sudo  
• **command > file.txt** Redirect output to file  
• **command >> file.txt** Append output to file  
• **command &** Run a command in background  
• **command1 && command2** Run multiple commands  
• **VAR=value** Set a variable  
• **echo $VAR** Echo a variable  
• **chmod +x script.sh** Make script executable  
• **./script.sh** Run a script
